    "body": "<!--To help us understand and resolve your issue, please fill out the form to the best of your ability. Feel free to delete the sections that do not apply.-->\r\n\r\n**Description of the problem**\r\n\r\nI am testing our build process on a Mac mini with an M1 chip (ARM architecture).  I am doing this without GDAL for now since at least for MacPorts the geos library fails to build (and libpvx does not support arm64 so **ffmpeg** cannot be installed - these have tickets and will be fixed soon I hope).\r\n\r\nI anticipated this compilation Eror:\r\n\r\n```\r\n../src/gmt_common_sighandler.c:178:14: error: no member named '__eip' in 'struct __darwin_arm_thread_state64'\r\n        array [0] = UC_IP (uc); /* caller's address */\r\n                    ^~~~~~~~~~\r\n../src/gmt_common_sighandler.c:62:56: note: expanded from macro 'UC_IP'\r\n#   define UC_IP(uc) ((void *) (uc)->uc_mcontext->__ss.__eip)\r\n                               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ ^\r\n```\r\n\r\nBasically, I need to the `__arm64__` equivalent of\r\n\r\n`#   define UC_IP(uc) ((void *) (uc)->uc_mcontext->__ss.__rip)`\r\n\r\n\r\nfor the M1 chip.  Could anyone with knowledge point me to a solution?",
